Linting:
	npm i eslint -D
	npm run lint -- --init
	npm run lint -- --fix
	https://eslint.org/docs/2.0.0/rules/
	npm i nyc
	
Best practices:
	Modlarity,
	Avoid synchronous calll
	Avoid task which is CPU extensive
	Unit testing and Linting =>use multiple rules
	Codecoverage =>nyc
	authenication
	Clustering (horizantal scaling)
	use prmises , asyn await more frequently for async operations
	maintain package.json(dependecies and script.tag)
	Use Enviornment variable , process.env.NODE_ENV, process.ENV_PORT
	Require all your dependencies up front
	use forever, pm2
	avoid console.log (while pushing for deployement)
	database optimization
	
